      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests for hemolysis transport equation; method of manufactured solutions applied to UDF.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy verified for Navier-Stokes solver only; no manufactured-solution test applied to the hemolysis power-law UDF. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI reported for hemolysis index QoI on three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh Richardson extrapolation performed; GCI for hemolysis index is 14% on the fine mesh, exceeding the 5% target. Spatial discretization error remains a significant contributor to total uncertainty budget. Achieved level 3 of 4 required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
