      "rationale": "Blood analog fluid properties reported but hematocrit variability across test runs not fully characterized. Inlet velocity profile assumed flat in simulation; experimental inlet turbulence intensity not measured. Achieved level 2 of 4 required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative metric (e.g., E_rms or agreement index) computed between predicted and measured hemolysis index with uncertainty bands on both simulation and experiment.",
      "rationale": "Point-by-point comparison performed at 5 operating conditions; mean absolute error 38% with no experimental uncertainty bars provided by the study. Systematic under-prediction near peak-shear regions limits confidence. Achieved level 2 of 4 required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (hemolysis index, pressure head) are identical to those required for the regulatory submission decision.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index is the primary QoI in both validation and COU. Pressure head is a secondary QoI. No surrogate QoIs employed. Minor gap: validation dataset does not include all five target operating points for the specific VAD configuration. Achieved level 3 of 4 required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
