      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence and round-off error quantified; residuals reduced by at least 6 orders of magnitude for all equations including hemolysis scalar.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored for momentum and continuity; hemolysis scalar residuals not separately tracked. Round-off error not assessed. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 of 4 required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent analyst review of simulation setup, boundary condition selection, and post-processing scripts; documented checklist with sign-off.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation setup performed. Single analyst executed all simulation and post-processing steps. Use error is an unmitigated epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 of 4 required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by comparison of multiple RANS/LES closures against hemolysis-relevant experimental data; hemolysis power-law constants validated against multiple independent datasets.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST turbulence model selected based on general pump literature without hemolysis-specific justification. Hemolysis power-law constants (Giersiepen et al.) are known to have significant inter-study variability. Model form uncertainty not formally bounded. Achieved level 2 of 5 required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain input parameters identified, probability distributions assigned from literature or measurement, and propagated through Monte Carlo UQ to yield hemolysis index prediction intervals.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed over inlet flow rate and rotational speed only; blood viscosity, hematocrit, and hemolysis model constants treated as fixed nominal values. Incomplete input uncertainty characterization limits validity of prediction intervals. Achieved level 2 of 5 required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Minimum of three independent experimental replicates per operating condition with statistical characterization of inter-sample variability.",
      "rationale": "Single experimental dataset available from FDA benchmark study; no replicate runs at the VAD-specific operating conditions. Inter-sample variability in hemolysis measurement not characterized. Epistemic gap flagged. Achieved level 1 of 4 required."
    },
