  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou2-vad-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-panel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite all seven assessed credibility factors achieving levels below their required thresholds and six factors remaining unassessed at MRL 5, the assessment is accepted with a mandatory remediation plan. The Monte Carlo UQ over inlet flow rate and rotational speed — along with the screening sensitivity study identifying rotational speed as the dominant hemolysis driver — provides partial uncertainty characterization sufficient to support a conditional acceptance. The panel requires closure of model form, model inputs, use error, and test sample gaps prior to regulatory submission. No structured sensitivity analysis node is linked in this package; the screening study is documented in the narrative only.",
